4573	ACT IV
4574	
4575	
4576	
4577	SCENE X	Between the two camps.
4578	
4579	
4580	[Enter MARK ANTONY and SCARUS, with their Army]
4581	
4582	MARK ANTONY	Their preparation is to-day by sea;
4583	We please them not by land.
4584	
4585	SCARUS	For both, my lord.
4586	
4587	MARK ANTONY	I would they'ld fight i' the fire or i' the air;
4588	We'ld fight there too. But this it is; our foot
4589	Upon the hills adjoining to the city
4590	Shall stay with us: order for sea is given;
4591	They have put forth the haven [           ]
4592	Where their appointment we may best discover,
4593	And look on their endeavour.
4594	
4595	[Exeunt]
4596	
