4602	
4603	ACT IV
4604	
4605	
4606	SCENE XI	Another part of the same.
4607	
4608	
4609	[Enter OCTAVIUS CAESAR, and his Army]
4610	
4611	OCTAVIUS CAESAR	But being charged, we will be still by land,
4612	Which, as I take't, we shall; for his best force
4613	Is forth to man his galleys. To the vales,
4614	And hold our best advantage.
4615	
4616	[Exeunt]
4617	
